quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The overflow Property[/h1]

As discussed earlier, every element on the page is a [b]box[/b]. If the height of the box is not set, the height of that box will grow as large as necessary to accommodate the content. 

[b]The HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<div>
This text is inside the div element, which has a blue 
background color and is floated to the left. We set a specific 
height and width for the div element, and as you can see, 
the content cannot fit. 
</div>[/code]
[b]The CSS: [/b] [code format="css" codeId="574"]div {
  [b]width:[/b] 150px;
  [b]height: [/b]150px;
  background-color: LightBlue;
  float: left;
}[/code]
[b]Result: [/b] [img id="2659" width="100%"]
[note]The CSS [b]overflow [/b]property specifies the behavior that occurs when an element's content overflows the element's box.[/note]

quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to produce horizontal and vertical scrollbars:
[!raw!]
div {
width: 150px;
height: 150px;
background-color: LightBlue;
float: left;
{0}: {1};
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The overflow Property Values[/h1]

There are four values for the overflow property: [b]visible[/b] (the default value), [b]scroll[/b], [b]hidden[/b], and [b]auto[/b]. 

The value [b]scroll [/b]results in clipped overflow, but a scrollbar is added, so the rest of the content may be seen.

[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="575"]div {
   width: 150px;
   height: 150px;
   background-color: LightBlue;
   float: left;
   [b]overflow: scroll;[/b]
}[/code]
The code above will produce both [b]horizontal [/b]and [b]vertical [/b]scrollbars: [img id="2660" width="100%"]

[h1]auto and hidden[/h1]

[b]auto [/b]- If overflow is clipped, a scroll-bar should be added to make it possible to see the rest of the content.
[b]hidden [/b]- The overflow is clipped, and the rest of the content will be invisible.

[b]The CSS:[/b][code format="css" codeId="576"]div {
   width: 150px;
   height: 150px;
   background-color: LightBlue;
   float: left;
   [b]overflow: hidden;[/b]
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2661" width="100%"]
[note]The default value for the overflow property is [b]visible[/b].[/note]
